HEADWORD: grovelling
<hw>grov"el*ling</hw></mhw>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Lying prone; low; debased; submissive in a self-abasing
manner.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>groveling</xex> creature.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cringing, wormlike, wormy.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

